commit.message: Moved backend to new repo to make Heroku deployment easier
Modified package.json so that the backend is the main script
Added backend express server wrapping around backdrop
Moved backdrop into separate repo. It is also published on NPM now as text-backdrop

Completely reworked backend so that it is now a callable node js module called backdrop. Now the front end can call backdrop directly with browserify, so there is no need for a server. Backdrop currently supports Yelp News and Image APIs, Wikipedia summary API, Indicio Named Entity, Keyword, and Text Tags
